    <div id='concert_image'>
      <h1>Park Slope Singers in Concert</h1>
      <h2>Elena Williamson, Music Director</h2>
      <img src="https://i.imgur.com/R4Jprqe.png" width="100%">
      <div>
        <p class="soloist"><strong>Katz Roy</strong>, Treble</p>
        <p class="soloist"><strong>Melanie Russell</strong>, Soprano</p>
        <p class="soloist"><strong>Tim Parsons</strong>, Countertenor</p>
        <p class="soloist"><strong>Gregorio Taniguchi</strong>, Tenor</p>
        <p class="soloist"><strong>Thomas McCargar</strong>, Bass</p>
        <p class="soloist">With harp, percussion, organ, and chorus</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p>
          After many postponements and too many Zoom sessions, we are happy to be back for our first live concert in over two years. We'll perform Leonard Bernstein's <em>Chichester Psalms</em>, along with Salamone Rossi's Renaissance setting of <em>Kaddish</em> and other pieces expressing the theme of Love and Remembrance by Maurice Duruflé, Randall Thompson, Virgil Thompson and Eric Whitacre.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our singers are vaccinated and will be tested the day before the first concert. Audience members must be vaccinated and wear a mask throughout the performance. We will follow all NYC COVID guidance, as well as any rules imposed by the venue.
        </p>
        <p>Admission: $20; Students and Seniors $15.</p></p>
      </div>
      <div id='concert_left'>
        <h2>Saturday, April 2, 3:00 PM</h2>
        <p class="concert_text">
          St. John’s Episcopal Church<br>
          139 St. John’s Place, Brooklyn NY
        </p>
        <a href="https://bpt.me/5386803" target="_blank">
